# .trivyignore — repo-wide Trivy suppression list
#
# Purpose: accept a specific finding (false positive, or a risk consciously accepted)
# WITHOUT lowering the HIGH/CRITICAL gate in the PR pipelines. The PR pipelines pass
# this file explicitly via --ignorefile; Trivy also auto-loads it when run from the
# repo root (e.g. local scans: `trivy image <image>`).
#
# Rules:
#   - One vulnerability/check ID per line (CVE-XXXX-NNNNN, AVD-DS-NNNN, etc.).
#   - EVERY entry must carry a comment: why it is safe to ignore, who accepted it,
#     and an expiry/review date. Remove entries as soon as a fix ships.
#   - Prefer fixing (bump base image / dependency) over ignoring. This file is the
#     exception path, not the default.
#
# Examples (keep commented out):
#   # False positive: package not reachable at runtime, accepted by @neesh 2026-07-06, review 2026-10-01
#   # CVE-2026-12345
#
#   # Dockerfile check: root user required for init step, mitigated by USER later in stage
#   # AVD-DS-0002

# (no active suppressions)
# smoke-test: PR validation trigger check (safe to remove)
